how can i set thunderbird to check for new messages in all of my imap folders stanford answers stanford university stanford answers how can i set thunderbird to check for new messages in all of my imap folders categories accounts and ids administrative applications anti virus and security computer operating systems connecting to the network desktop hardware and support email and calendar help desk restricted information on it services software at stanford stanford hospital and clinics telephones and cable tv unix systems and software web services user login login with your sunet id home how can i set thunderbird to check for new messages in all of my imap folders search this site thunderbird like most mail programs by default just checks for new mail in the inbox you can set thunderbird to check for new messages in all of your imap folders this way you can see more easily when new mail has arrived and has been placed by your filters into other mailboxes under tools options advanced click the config editor button and set the mail check_all_imap_folders_for_new preference to true to set thunderbird to check for new messages in all of your imap folders 1 in thunderbird choose tools options 2 in the advanced tab click config editor 3 search for the preference mail check_all_imap_folders_for_new 4 set the preference to true double click on the settings to toggle the value between true and false note do not change this setting unless you re using webmail with server side filters changing this setting to true can negatively affect thunderbird performance for more information see configuring your email program if you need more help submit a helpsu request or call 5 help thunderbird at stanford stanford university 450 serra mall stanford california 94305 650 723 2300 terms of use copyright complaints
